<FIRST>u a PM-WanderingPlane CORRECTIVE   07-21 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wandering Plane, CORRECTIVE,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: Members who used a0607 of July 19, under a Fort Lauderdale,
Fla., dateline, are asked to use the following story. The story was corrected
late in the PMs cycle July 19.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In some versions of an Associated
Press story July 19, which cited a published report, it was
erroneously reported that a federal drug task force operating under
drug czar William Bennett's office started an investigation into
lawyer Thomas Root's activities two days before his plane ditched
in Bahamian waters.
   Drug Enforcement Administration spokesman Mario Perez says the
task force operates under the auspices of the DEA, not of Bennett's
office. He said Virginia police, part of the task force, had passed
along information to the DEA about a search of Root's airline
hangar that they said found guns and a can of ether, but the task
force had not initiated a formal investigation.
</TEXT>
