<HEAD>Top German Diplomat In Intensive Care After Mild Heart Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Foreign Minister Hans-Dietrich
Genscher was in intensive care today after suffering a mild heart
attack, spokesmen said.
   The mass-circulation newspaper Bild quoted Genscher's main
spokesman, Juergen Chrobog, as saying the foreign minister will
probably require doctor's care ``for several weeks.''
   Another Foreign Ministry spokesman, Hanns Schumacher, said the
62-year-old Genscher was being treated in an intensive care unit of
a Bonn hospital: ``That is the usual procedure in a case like
this.''
   Schumacher said it was not known exactly how long the foreign
minister would remain hospitalized.
   Genscher complained of acute chest pains Thursday and was taken
to a Bonn hospital, where doctors determined he had suffered a mild
heart attack.
