<HEAD>Bush Picks Hostler for Ambassador to Bahrain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Friday announced he will
nominate Charles Warren Hostler as ambassador to Bahrain and Mark
Gregory Hambley as emissary to Qatar.
   Hambley is consul general in Alexandria, Egypt, and has served
in postings in Vietnam, Lebanon, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Yemen,
Tunisia and Libya. He received the State Department's Meritorious
Honor award in 1976 and 1979.
