Commission. A former Secret Service agent, he is director of
special investigations in the General Accounting Office, and
previously worked as operations director in the Labor Department's
labor racketeering division and as a staff director for the
president's Commission on Organized Crime.
   _J. Clarence Davies as assistant administrator of the
Environmental Protection Agency for policy and evaluation. He is
executive vice president of the Conservation Foundation and
previously was senior staff member for the Council on Environmental
Quality and a professor of politics at Princeton University.
   _Gordon K. Durnil as commissioner on the International Joint
Commission involving the United States and Canada. An attorney and
businessman, he is chairman of the Indiana Republican Party.
