<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
151,750 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
93,782, Ward's Automotive Reports said.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 156,536 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said Thursday.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 82,328 cars this week,
compared with 55,937 a week ago and 88,055 in the same week in 1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 69,422,
compared with last week's 37,845 and last year's 68,481.
   Canadian automakers were to build 12,510 cars this week, down
from 12,723 a week ago and up from last year's 5,444.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 5,400, compared
with 6,737 a week ago and 5,488 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
