<FILEID>AP-NR-07-21-89 1704EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Ralston     07-21 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Ralston,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ralson Purina Reports Quarterly Results</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ralston Purina Co. on Friday reported higher
profits and revenue for its third fiscal quarter.
   For the period ended June 30, net income totaled $83.8 million,
or $1.27 a share, up 9 percent from $77.2 million, or $1.13 a share
in the comparable 1988 period. The company reported $4.1 million
made from discontinued operations.
   Sales jumped 15 percent to $1.62 billion from $1.41 billion in
the year-ago period.
   Ralston Purina said volume increases from its Eveready Battery
operation during the quarter were significant.
   For the first nine months of 1989, net income totaled $306
million, or $4.64 a share from continuing operations, up from $284
million, or $4.11 a share in the year-ago period. The company
reported $71.3 million made from discontinued operations.
   Revenue totaled $4.89 billion, up from $4.32 billion in the
first nine months 1988.
</TEXT>
