<FILEID>AP-NR-07-21-89 2145EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Phones     07-21 0237</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Phones,0247</SECOND>
<HEAD>U S West Earnings Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U S West on Friday reported lower net income in
the second quarter due to a one-time gain in the year-ago period
but noted that its non-telephone operations continue to grow.
   For the period ended June 30, U S West reported earnings of
$258.6 million, or $1.42 a share, down 23 percent from net income
of $336.3 million, or $1.83 a share a year ago.
   Excluding last year's one-time after-tax gain of $88.7 million
from the sale of its 19 percent interest in U S West NewVector
Group, U S West said net income rose 4.4 percent.
   Total revenue for the quarter totaled $2.4 billion, up 4 percent
from $2.3 billion for the comparable period last year.
   Although a little more than 90 percent of U S West revenues come
from its telephone operations, it also owns companies involved in
real estate, financial services, computer software, cellular
telephones and other businesses.
   ``Our 1989 earnings were right where we expected them to be,''
said U S West Chief Executive Jack McAllister in a statement. ``Our
growth in earnings per share continues to come from our
non-telephone operations, and we don't expect that to change.''
   For the six months, net income totaled $508.2 million, or $2.78
a share on revenues of $4.83 billion, compared with profit of
$576.8 million, or $3.13 a share on revenues of $4.44 billion.
</TEXT>
