<HEAD>Mortgage Rates Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages currently are
averaging 9.87 percent, according to a national survey released
Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was up from a rate of 9.82 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.72 percent this week, down from 8.73
percent the week before, Freddie Mac said.
